Making sure the player actually gets experience for killing the creature![/b]
You can save and close the client.java now :)
Okay. 
Go to NpcHandler.java and search for 
[code]
if (npcs[i].npcType
[/code]
There should be some sort of code below that, if not keep looking for it.
It should look like this:
[code]
}
if (npcs[i].npcType == 87 && temp.taskID == 87) {
temp.addSkillXP(1500, 18);
temp.taskAmount -= 1;
if (temp.taskAmount == 0 || temp.taskAmount == 1) {
temp.taskID = -1;
temp.taskAmount = -1;
temp.sM("You have completed your task. Talk to Vannaka to get a new one.");
}
[/code]

Okay i'm going to tell you what to do here then explain it. :)
First of all, remember the NPC id's that you used as your task-sets earlier....1624, 1616, 1615 etc.
Now depending on the groups you put them in your going to want to set the Experience correspondingly so here is an example for you. For dust devils which are...on average level 65 Slayer to kill.

[code]
}
if (npcs[i].npcType == 1624 && temp.taskID == 1624) {
temp.addSkillXP(15600, 18);
temp.taskAmount -= 1;
if (temp.taskAmount == 0 || temp.taskAmount == 1) {
temp.taskID = -1;
temp.taskAmount = -1;
temp.sM("You have completed your task. Talk to Duradel to get a new one.");
}
[/code]


Not much difference from the first example huh? Thats because adding slayer tasks like this is much simpler than everyone thinks. Now to do the others you can copy and paste that all down then change the experience rates and NPC ID's. You may also notice that i have changed the slayer master. This is because i find on many sources Duradel is the easiest master. 

Explanation:

[code]
if (npcs[i].npcType == 1624 && temp.taskID == 1624) {
[/code]
This is pretty straight forward. It is the NPC ID. make sure you change BOTH of these!! This is critical to your player getting the correct experience.

[code]
temp.addSkillXP(15600, 18);
[/code]
This is the experience the player will gain for killing it. the 15600 is the experience and the 18 is the level. Obviously you can change it if you were doing another skill but this is a slayer Tutorial!

[code]
temp.taskAmount -= 1;
[/code]
This tells the client to deduct a creature from your slayer task total.

[code]
if (temp.taskAmount == 0 || temp.taskAmount == 1) {
temp.taskID = -1;
temp.taskAmount = -1;
temp.sM("You have completed your task. Talk to Duradel to get a new one.");
[/code]
This basically all works together. The first bit is checking to see if you are done, then the two other bits are telling the client you are done then the final bit is actually telling the player that your task is complete.

[b]EXTRA'S[/b]
Setting extra Slayer Task options
Okay so your getting a bit bored of the current task set and you have a couple of really good Slayers on your server who want something different!
Heres how to do this:
Open Client.java
First of all do ctrl + f and type in lowtask, just as if your adding the NPC's to your task-set.
You should get something like this again:
[code] 
 public int[] lowTask = { 90, 1616};
 public int[] mediumTask = { 90, 1624};
 public int[] highTask = {1624, 1615};
 public int taskID = -1;
 public int taskAmount = -1;
[/code]
Now just add in here the following line of code:
[code]
	public int[] extremeTask = { 2783, 50 };
[/code]

This is saying that there is an extremtask! which could be for people with slayer levels of upto 99!
The task-set i have set is Dark Beasts and King Black Dragons.
Don't close and compile yet, theres still alot to do!
Scroll down from that until you see
[code]

	public int randomHighTask() 
	{
		return highTask[(int) (Math.random() * highTask.length)];
	}
[/code]

Okay cop that code (with BOTH brackets) and paste it directly below, so it looks alligned with everything else.
Then change HighTask to extremetask.
It should look like this:
[code]
	public int randomExtremeTask()
	{
		return extremeTask[(int) (Math.random() * extremeTask.length)];
	}
[/code]
Explanation:
This is basically telling the client that there is a task called extremetask and that it should imply it.

Setting the level requirements for the task:
do ctrl + f and search for 
